---
import FeatureCard from "../components/FeatureCard.astro";
import SectionHeading from "../components/SectionHeading.astro";
import CommandBlock from "../components/react/CommandBlock";
import HeroShowcase from "../components/react/HeroShowcase";
import TourScroller from "../components/react/TourScroller";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { architectureSteps, docsPreview, durableSurfaces, quickstartSteps, tourChapters } from "../site.config";
---

<BaseLayout
  activeNav="/"
  description="Maestro is a local-first orchestration control plane for Codex and ChatGPT with an embedded dashboard, MCP bridge, and durable SQLite-backed tracker."
  path="/"
  title="Maestro"
>
  <section class="section-shell grid gap-10 pb-18 pt-10 md:pb-24 md:pt-16 lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_minmax(0,0.95fr)] lg:items-center">
    <div>
      <h1 class="max-w-4xl font-display text-[clamp(3.2rem,8vw,5.6rem)] font-semibold leading-[0.96] tracking-tight text-white">
        Local-first orchestration for Codex and ChatGPT.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-8 text-[var(--muted)] md:text-xl">
        Maestro combines a durable SQLite-backed tracker, an MCP attach point, and a live control center so you can move from workflow bootstrap to active orchestration without leaving your own machine.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="button-primary" href="/docs/quickstart">Start with quickstart</a>
        <a class="button-secondary" href="/docs">Open documentation</a>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="panel-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[var(--muted)]">Install</p>
          <p class="mt-2 font-mono text-sm text-white">npm install -g @olhapi/maestro</p>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[var(--muted)]">Workflow</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white">Bootstrap a repo-local WORKFLOW.md and keep the loop visible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[var(--muted)]">Control Center</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white">Monitor runs, retries, and token burn in one surface.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <HeroShowcase client:visible quickstartSteps={quickstartSteps} surfaces={durableSurfaces} />
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell pb-18 md:pb-24">
    <SectionHeading
      description="The product story is intentionally simple: keep work local, expose it to agents through MCP, and keep enough runtime context visible to supervise the loop."
      title="One control plane, three surfaces that stay aligned."
    />
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
      {durableSurfaces.map((surface) => <FeatureCard description={surface.description} title={surface.title} />)}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell pb-18 md:pb-24">
    <SectionHeading
      description="The dashboard is not decorative chrome. It is the supervision surface for a live orchestration loop, so the walkthrough focuses on how state, work routing, issue detail, and sessions fit together."
      title="Read the queue, route work, and inspect execution without losing context."
    />
    <div class="mt-8">
      <TourScroller client:visible chapters={tourChapters} mode="home" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell pb-18 md:pb-24">
    <SectionHeading
      description="The homepage conversion path is direct on purpose: install, bootstrap the workflow file, and launch the daemon with an observability port."
      title="Three commands to move from blank repo to visible orchestration."
    />
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-3">
      {quickstartSteps.map((step) => <CommandBlock client:load command={step.command} detail={step.detail} title={step.title} />)}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell pb-18 md:pb-24">
    <SectionHeading
      description="The architecture stays compact. The attach path, daemon, tracker, and agent runner are close enough that you can explain the whole loop on one screen."
      title="Keep the system shape legible even when the work itself gets messy."
    />
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_minmax(0,0.95fr)]">
      <div class="panel p-6 md:p-8">
        <p class="kicker">Runtime path</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {architectureSteps.map((step, index) => (
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex size-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[rgba(196,255,87,0.25)] bg-[rgba(196,255,87,0.1)] font-display text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--accent-strong)]">
                {index + 1}
              </div>
              <p class="pt-2 text-base leading-7 text-[var(--muted)]">{step}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="panel p-6 md:p-8">
        <p class="kicker">Architecture</p>
        <pre class="overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/8 bg-black/35 p-5 font-mono text-sm text-[var(--muted-strong)]"><code>{`Codex or ChatGPT (via MCP)
        |
        v
maestro mcp (stdio bridge)
        |
        v
maestro run daemon <-> SQLite Kanban store
        |
        v
Orchestrator -> workspace lifecycle -> agent runner
        ^
        |
   WORKFLOW.md`}</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell pb-18 md:pb-24">
    <SectionHeading
      description="The docs are organized around the path a new builder actually takes: install, quickstart, understand the runtime model, then tune workflow and operations details."
      title="Documentation stays one click from the product story."
    />
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
      {docsPreview.map((item) => <FeatureCard description={item.description} href={item.href} title={item.title} />)}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell pb-18">
    <div class="panel grid gap-6 p-8 md:grid-cols-[1fr_auto] md:items-end md:p-10">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white md:text-5xl">
          Start with quickstart, then stay in the docs until the loop feels boring.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-[var(--muted)] md:text-lg">
          The goal is not a flashy landing page disconnected from the product. It is an engaging front door that turns directly into durable docs and the live product walkthrough on this page.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="button-primary" href="/docs/quickstart">Read quickstart</a>
        <a class="button-secondary" href="/docs">Browse docs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
